kerchunk (1.0.2-1) stable; urgency=medium

  * Wall-clock scheduler and managed thread pool
  * Frame-synchronized FLEX paging (capcode % 128 frame alignment)
  * FLEX 'now' command for immediate TX (bypass scheduler)
  * POCSAG/FLEX/APRS tx_level config and modulation mode (baseband/FSK)
  * POCSAG/FLEX de-emphasis config for direct FM modulators
  * QUEUE_FLAG_NO_TAIL to suppress courtesy tone on data TX
  * Dynamic dashboard UI with module-registered controls
  * 48kHz default sample rate, configurable via config
  * TX CTCSS/DCS encoding moved to mod_tones
  * Web audio fix at 48kHz (AudioWorklet sample rate)
  * Git hash in version string and deb package version
  * 12 critical/high + 11 medium security fixes from audit
  * Detailed CLI help text for all module commands
  * Burst tone CLI commands in mod_txcode
  * Heartbeat event and version in admin dashboard
  * Remove GMRS-specific branding from service/docs
  * Requires libpocsag >= 1.0.2, libflex >= 1.0.2, libaprs >= 1.0.2

 -- Brian West <brian@kerchunk.net>  Wed, 02 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000

kerchunk (1.0.1-1) stable; urgency=medium

  * Fix COR polarity: CM108 inverts internally, default now active_high
  * Fix COR HID read: drain all queued reports, use last state
  * Fix PTT pin: GPIO2 for CM108 RIM-Lite (was wrong pin)
  * Fix module install path: /usr/lib/kerchunk (was multiarch path)
  * Fix socket path: /run/kerchunk/kerchunk.sock
  * Fix audio jitter: pad partial queue drain frames with silence
  * Fix resampler underrun: ramp down instead of hard zero (clicks)
  * Add kerchunk-diag: standalone PTT/audio/COR diagnostic tool
  * Add HID debug logging for COR troubleshooting
  * Use /dev/rimlite udev symlink as default HID device
  * Update README with RIM-Lite GPIO mapping and polarity notes

 -- Brian West <brian@kerchunk.net>  Sun, 29 Mar 2026 20:00:00 -0500

kerchunk (1.0.0-1) stable; urgency=medium

  * Initial Debian package release
  * kerchunkd GMRS/HAM repeater controller daemon
  * kerchunk CLI for runtime control
  * 24 dynamically loaded modules
  * Embedded HTTPS web dashboard with WebSocket audio
  * FCC 95.1751 compliant CW ID and voice identification
  * NWS alert monitoring with TTS announcements
  * Systemd service with security hardening

 -- Brian West <brian@kerchunk.net>  Fri, 27 Mar 2026 12:00:00 -0500
